items.title: Kipnis in center is smart risk behind strong staff
items.summary: Cleveland may be taking a risk by moving Jason Kipnis to center field two weeks before the playoffs start, but it's a calculated risk. Thanks to the dominating Tribe pitching staff, there's just not as many difficult balls in play against Cleveland as you'd think.

items.title: Schmidt's vision inspired iconic red bird logo
items.summary: There are few logos in baseball as closely linked to a team as the "Birds on the Bat" is to the Cardinals. And that's thanks to Allie May Schmidt's inspired decision to create cardinal centerpieces with cardboard and twine for an event featuring then-GM Branch Rickey in 1921.

items.title: Goldschmidt a beacon of endurance
items.summary: The pain in his right elbow persisted, but Paul Goldschmidt persevered. The postseason bound D-backs avoided a September scare two weeks ago when their All-Star first baseman and National League MVP candidate underwent an MRI that revealed inflammation in his left elbow but no structural damage, forcing him to miss five games.
